sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1489006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
CvGal1 is from the Crasseoterra virginica genome, codon optimized for E. coli expression.
OmpA is from the E. coli genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CvGal1 fused to OmpA in order to anchor it in the membrane.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Gibson overhangs were designed for Gibson assembly
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Iowis Zhu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1489002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Part sequence is from BBa_K103006, which originally comes from the E. coli genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Outer membrane protein A (OmpA) is a common outer membrane protein found in bacteria that serves various purposes. For our purposes, the beta-barrel transmembrane domain can be utilized to anchor otherwise soluble proteins in the outer cell membrane. Lpp serves to direct the fusion protein, while a unstructured linker (GGGSGGGS) serves to separate OmpA from its cargo in order to avoid interactions between the two proteins.
The expressed protein is structurally identical to BBa_K103006. This version of the biobrick has been moved into the new backbone, pSB1C3, which contains the gene for chloramphenicol resistance. This resistance gene contains an internal SacI site, making the SacI site at the end of the gene almost unusable for RE cloning. BBa_K1489003 mutagenizes this SacI site into a KasI in order to avoid this issue.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: SacI site is kept in this version of Lpp-OmpA-Linker, is removed in BBa_K1489003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Iowis Zhu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1489005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genome of Crasseoterra virginica, optimized for E. coli expression
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Soluble beta-galactoside binding protein (galectin) originally from Crasseoterra virginica. Believed to expressed both intracellularly and extracellularly, where they serve to binding various types of n-acetylgalactosamines and initialize signal cascades. Believed to be a tetramer in its active form, as is true with most invertebrate galectins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: PstI site in the coding sequence had to be redesigned.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Iowis Zhu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa
